1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,360
Hello, English learners.
你好，英语学习者。

2
00:00:03,360 --> 00:00:04,720
Welcome back to EnglishPod.
欢迎回到EnglishPod。

3
00:00:04,720 --> 00:00:05,840
My name is Marco.
我是Marco。

4
00:00:05,840 --> 00:00:07,120
And I'm Erica.
我是Erica。

5
00:00:07,120 --> 00:00:10,560
And today with Erica, we're bringing you a great lesson about time.
今天和Erica一起，我们为大家带来一堂关于时间的精彩课程。

6
00:00:10,560 --> 00:00:11,560
You need more of it.
你需要更多时间。

7
00:00:11,560 --> 00:00:12,880
We need more time, right?
我们需要更多时间，对吧？

8
00:00:12,880 --> 00:00:13,880
Yeah.
是的。

9
00:00:13,880 --> 00:00:16,440
So we're going to be teaching you how you can ask for more time.
所以我们将教你如何请求更多时间。

10
00:00:16,440 --> 00:00:21,280
If you're working on a project at work and you can't finish it on time, you have to ask
如果你在工作中负责一个项目，无法按时完成，你必须向老板请求更多时间。

11
00:00:21,280 --> 00:00:23,880
your boss for more time.
向你的老板请求更多时间。

12
00:00:23,880 --> 00:00:24,880
Right.
没错。

13
00:00:24,880 --> 00:00:30,240
So in our dialogue, Casey needs more time to put together a press kit.
所以在我们的对话中，Casey需要更多时间来准备一个媒体资料包。

14
00:00:30,240 --> 00:00:31,240
What's a press kit?
什么是媒体资料包？

15
00:00:31,240 --> 00:00:32,240
Good question.
好问题。

16
00:00:32,240 --> 00:00:36,680
A press kit is something the marketing department will put together.
媒体资料包是市场部会准备的东西。

17
00:00:36,680 --> 00:00:41,680
Basically pictures, logos, information about the company.
基本上包括图片、标志、公司信息。

18
00:00:41,680 --> 00:00:45,760
So when a newspaper or a magazine wants to write an article about them, so they have
所以当报纸或杂志想写一篇关于他们的文章时，他们已经有准备好的资料可以提供给报纸或杂志。

19
00:00:45,760 --> 00:00:49,720
something already prepared that they could give the newspaper or magazine.
已经准备好的东西，可以给报纸或杂志。

20
00:00:49,720 --> 00:00:50,800
Okay.
好的。

21
00:00:50,800 --> 00:00:53,940
So let's listen to our dialogue for the first time.
那么让我们第一次听我们的对话。

22
00:00:53,940 --> 00:00:57,520
And as always, it's going to be at a normal speed, so it might be a little bit difficult
和往常一样，它会以正常语速进行，所以可能有点难理解。

23
00:00:57,520 --> 00:00:58,520
to understand.
有点难理解。

24
