例子一。

182
00:08:08,240 --> 00:08:15,880
I've been putting off this project for a week and it's due tomorrow.
我把这个项目推迟了一周，明天就要交了。

183
00:08:15,880 --> 00:08:17,640
Example two.
例子二。

184
00:08:17,640 --> 00:08:21,920
Can we put off our meeting until next week?
我们能推迟会议到下周吗？

185
00:08:21,920 --> 00:08:26,880
I'm too busy right now.
我现在太忙了。

186
00:08:26,880 --> 00:08:30,080
Example three.
例子三。

187
00:08:30,080 --> 00:08:37,320
I've been putting off my email all day and now I have 50 messages to respond to.
我一整天都在推迟处理邮件，现在有50条消息要回复。

188
00:08:37,320 --> 00:08:41,240
So Marco, when you put something off, you leave it for later.
所以马可，当你推迟某事时，你把它留到以后做。

189
00:08:41,240 --> 00:08:42,240
Okay.
好的。

190
00:08:42,240 --> 00:08:43,240
Right.
对。

191
00:08:43,240 --> 00:08:47,360
I'm going to write a report today, but I'm going to put it off till tomorrow.
我今天要写报告，但我要推迟到明天。

192
00:08:47,360 --> 00:08:48,800
So you're going to do it tomorrow.
所以你打算明天做。

193
00:08:48,800 --> 00:08:49,800
I'll do it tomorrow.
我明天做。

194
00:08:49,800 --> 00:08:53,880
Okay, so we've seen some really great words and some really good phrases.
好的，我们学到了一些很棒的单词和短语。

195
00:08:53,880 --> 00:08:57,920
So now let's listen to our dialogue for the last time and then we'll come back and talk
现在让我们最后一次听对话，然后回来再聊

196
00:08:57,920 --> 00:09:04,480
some more.
更多内容。

197
00:09:04,480 --> 00:09:11,000
So Casey, how are things going with the photos for the press kit?
凯西，新闻资料包的照片进展如何？

198
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:15,080
Yeah, I've been meaning to talk to you about that.
嗯，我正想和你谈这件事。

199
00:09:15,080 --> 00:09:19,040
I might need to ask for an extension on that deadline.
我可能需要申请延期。

200
00:09:19,040 --> 00:09:22,240
You've had over a month to get this finalized.
你已经有一个多月的时间来完成这件事了。

201
00:09:22,240 --> 00:09:24,360
Why are things delayed?
为什么事情都延迟了？

202
00:09:24,360 --> 00:09:29,360
Well, the thing is we ran into a lot of problems.
嗯，问题是我们遇到了很多麻烦。

203
00:09:29,360 --> 00:09:31,480
I'm not looking for excuses here.
我不是在找借口。

204
00:09:31,480 --> 00:09:34,200
I just want to get this finished on time.
我只想按时完成这件事。

205
00:09:34,200 --> 00:09:35,240
I know.
我知道。

206
00:09:35,240 --> 00:09:40,000
And I apologize for the delay, but some things were just beyond my control.
我为延迟道歉，但有些事情确实超出了我的控制。

207
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:44,880
I had trouble booking the photographer and then Michael was sick for three weeks, so
我预约摄影师时遇到了麻烦，然后迈克尔病了三周，所以

208
00:09:44,880 --> 00:09:47,600
I couldn't include him in the photos.
我无法让他参与拍照。

209
00:09:47,600 --> 00:09:52,480
And the design team lost all the files, so I had to redo the pictures.
而且设计团队丢失了所有文件，所以我不得不重做图片。

210
00:09:52,480 --> 00:09:55,320
I'm not going to put this off any longer, Casey.
我不会再拖延了，凯西。

211
00:09:55,320 --> 00:09:58,320
I want those photos ASAP.
我尽快要那些照片。

212
00:09:58,320 --> 00:10:09,360
Well, Marco, do you think that Casey's reasons for being late are good?
嗯，马可，你觉得凯西迟到的理由合理吗？

213
00:10:09,360 --> 00:10:15,240
I think so, because it wasn't really her fault, the whole situation with the photographer.
我觉得合理，因为那真的不是她的错，整件事都是摄影师的问题。

214
00:10:15,240 --> 00:10:18,920
And then one of her co-workers was sick for three weeks.
然后她有个同事病了三周。

215
00:10:18,920 --> 00:10:20,160
It's not really her fault, right?
这真的不是她的错，对吧？

216
00:10:20,160 --> 00:10:24,120
Right, but maybe the boss thinks that she's making excuses.
对，但也许老板觉得她在找借口。

217
00:10:24,120 --> 00:10:26,080
Maybe she's making excuses.
也许她在找借口。

218
00:10:26,080 --> 00:10:27,080
That's really common.
这很常见。

219
00:10:27,080 --> 00:10:31,560
Like, for example, when we were kids, you would say, oh, you know, my dog ate my homework.
比如，我们小时候，你会说，哦，你知道，我的狗吃了我的作业。

220
00:10:31,560 --> 00:10:34,840
Right, but that really happened to me once.
对，但那真的在我身上发生过一次。

221
00:10:34,840 --> 00:10:35,840
Your dog ate your homework?
你的狗吃了你的作业？

222
00:10:35,840 --> 00:10:37,120
My cat ate my homework.
我的猫吃了我的作业。

223
00:10:37,120 --> 00:10:38,280
Your cat ate your homework?
你的猫吃了你的作业？

224
00:10:38,280 --> 00:10:39,280
Yeah.
是啊。

225
00:10:39,280 --> 00:10:40,280
What did your teacher say?
你老师怎么说？

226
00:10:40,280 --> 00:10:43,840
Well, actually, I was a really good student, so my teacher believed me.
嗯，其实我是个很好的学生，所以老师相信了我。

227
00:10:43,840 --> 00:10:46,760
Well, my teacher wouldn't have believed me.
我老师可不会相信我。

228
00:10:46,760 --> 00:10:47,760
Really?
真的吗？

229
00:10:47,760 --> 00:10:48,760
No, no.
不，不。

230
00:10:48,760 --> 00:10:50,920
She would have called my parents, most likely.
她很可能会给我父母打电话。

231
00:10:50,920 --> 00:10:55,040
My cat really did eat my homework, and I just left it on the table, and it chewed it all
我的猫真的吃了我的作业，我就把它放在桌子上，它全给嚼了

232
00:10:55,040 --> 00:10:56,040
up.
烂了。

233
00:10:56,040 --> 00:10:57,040
That's weird.
真奇怪。

234
00:10:57,040 --> 00:10:58,040
Why would your cat do that?
你的猫为什么会那样做？

235
00:10:58,040 --> 00:10:59,040
I don't know.
我不知道。

236
00:10:59,040 --> 00:11:00,040
A lot of weird excuses out there.
外面有很多奇怪的借口。

237
00:11:00,040 --> 00:11:01,040
Yeah.
是啊。

238
00:11:01,040 --> 00:11:02,640
I was abducted by aliens.
我被外星人绑架了。

239
00:11:02,640 --> 00:11:05,680
My mom accidentally mailed my homework to Africa.
我妈妈不小心把我的作业寄到了非洲。

240
00:11:05,680 --> 00:11:06,680
Really?
真的吗？

241
00:11:06,680 --> 00:11:07,680
Yeah.
是的。

242
00:11:07,680 --> 00:11:08,680
This happened to you?
你遇到过这种事？

243
00:11:08,680 --> 00:11:09,680
Yeah.
是的。

244
00:11:09,680 --> 00:11:10,680
Writing, creative excuses.
编造有创意的借口。

245
00:11:10,680 --> 00:11:13,840
Well, I want to hear from our listeners.
嗯，我想听听听众们的说法。

246
00:11:13,840 --> 00:11:18,000
I want to know what excuses they've used for being late with something.
我想知道他们因为什么事情迟到时用过什么借口。

247
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:21,280
So send us your excuses, send us your comments and questions.
所以请把你的借口、评论和问题发给我们。

248
00:11:21,280 --> 00:11:25,440
Go to our website at EnglishPod.com, where Eric and I are always there to answer your
访问我们的网站 EnglishPod.com，我和 Eric 随时在那里回答你的

249
00:11:25,440 --> 00:11:26,440
questions.
问题。

250
00:11:26,440 --> 00:11:29,360
That's right, Marco, and this is an elementary lesson, right?
没错，Marco，这是一节初级课程，对吧？

251
00:11:29,360 --> 00:11:30,360
Exactly.
正是。

252
00:11:30,360 --> 00:11:37,280
But we also have intermediate and upper intermediate and advanced lessons for you more fluent English
但我们也有中级、中高级和高级课程，适合英语更流利的

253
00:11:37,280 --> 00:11:38,280
speakers.
学习者。

254
00:11:38,280 --> 00:11:39,280
Exactly.
正是。

255
00:11:39,280 --> 00:11:42,760
So if you're listening to us on iTunes, be sure to visit our website and come see what
所以如果你在 iTunes 上收听我们，一定要访问我们的网站，看看

256
00:11:42,760 --> 00:11:43,760
else we have to offer.
我们还提供什么。

257
00:11:43,760 --> 00:12:12,800
Well, I think we're out of time, but until next time, it's goodbye.
好了，时间到了，下次再见，拜拜。
